# Inventory scan workflows

Keep **two separate workflows**. Do not merge them into one form.

## 1. Mobile QR Scan (field speed)

**Entry:** `render_inventory_scan_page()` in `inventory_scan.py`  
**Route:** `?scan=inventory` / inventory QR deep link (`inventory_scan_route_active`)

**UI — only:**
- Qty (with − / + steppers)
- Job / Shop dropdown (`Shop` first, then **all** jobs — any status)
- Enter

**Defaults (hidden):**
- Action = `issue_to_job` (job) or Shop Use (`shop`)
- Persist structured destination on save:
  - `destination_type` = `shop` or `job`
  - `job_id` = `null` for Shop, selected job uuid for Job
- Scanner name/phone from profile or device
- No notes, no action picker, no admin checkboxes on screen

**Goal:** Fast field issue-to-job after scanning a QR code.

**Images:** Use `render_inventory_item_thumbnail` / `get_inventory_image_url` only — see `inventory-item-images.mdc`.

## 2. Full Inventory Action (office / admin)

**Entry:** `_render_inventory_scan_inner()` — **Scan Inventory** module page  
**Also:** Inventory module issue flows, job materials UI admin controls

**UI includes:**
- Action / issue type
- Notes
- Person / device / manual actor
- Phone (where applicable)
- Allow over on-hand (admin)
- Check-in / check-out / tool panels

**Goal:** Corrections, admin overrides, and non-QR workflows.

## When changing behavior

| Change | Where |
|--------|--------|
| Simpler mobile UX | `render_inventory_scan_page` only |
| New action types, audit fields, overrides | Full workflow only |
| Shared services | `inventory_service`, `job_materials_service` |

Never add Action/notes/phone fields back to the mobile QR form unless explicitly requested.
